19/09/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Local prosecutors have charged fugitive tycoon Bogoljub Karic and 15 other people with embezzling funds from mobile phone operator Mobtel, local media reported on Saturday (September 18th). 
Among those charged is Bogoljub Karic's brother, Sreten. 
Both of them left the country in 2006. 
The Karic brothers are suspected of having transferred more than 60m euros from Mobtel account to accounts of BK Group and other private accounts. 
(Tanjug, Blic, RTS, B92, AFP - 18/09/10)
